all over it.

158
00:14:09,196 --> 00:14:10,371
[ Laughs ]

159
00:14:10,414 --> 00:14:13,287
[ Insects chirping ]

160
00:14:15,463 --> 00:14:17,769
Your dad, he was a cool guy.

161
00:14:17,813 --> 00:14:20,076
I remember staying
with your parents

162
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:23,210
when I was younger.

163
00:14:23,253 --> 00:14:25,429
He was a funny guy.

164
00:14:25,473 --> 00:14:28,693
I remember this one time.

165
00:14:28,737 --> 00:14:31,087
He had been drinking
all afternoon,

166
00:14:31,131 --> 00:14:33,785
and there was
this tornado warning,

167
00:14:33,829 --> 00:14:37,702
and I was freaking out,
crying and shit.

168
00:14:37,746 --> 00:14:40,488
And he came over to me
and told me not to worry,

169
00:14:40,531 --> 00:14:43,186
that he knew a dance
that was gonna protect US

170
00:14:43,230 --> 00:14:45,362
from the tornado.

171
00:14:45,406 --> 00:14:47,234
And he went out
into the front yard,

172
00:14:47,277 --> 00:14:51,020
started dancing
and singing and shit.

173
00:14:51,064 --> 00:14:55,807
And that tornado...
It never came.

174
00:14:58,245 --> 00:15:01,204
When I was older,
your mom told me he was watching

175
00:15:01,248 --> 00:15:03,380
the weather channel
with Gary england.

176
00:15:03,424 --> 00:15:04,686
[ Exhales sharply ]

177
00:15:04,729 --> 00:15:06,688
He knew that tornado
was never coming.

178
00:15:06,731 --> 00:15:08,733
[ Both laugh ]

179
00:15:11,432 --> 00:15:13,086
[ Chuckles ]

180
00:15:13,129 --> 00:15:14,957
All right, here you go.

181
00:15:15,001 --> 00:15:18,265
Kick the tires
and light the fires, boy.

182
00:15:22,008 --> 00:15:24,227
-Hey, Jim?

183
00:15:24,271 --> 00:15:26,273
-Yeah?

184
00:15:28,318 --> 00:15:31,017
-You ever feel like...

185
00:15:31,060 --> 00:15:33,410
Just getting
the fuck out of here?

186
00:15:33,454 --> 00:15:36,457
-Yeah.

187
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:39,329
But where would I go?

188
00:15:39,373 --> 00:15:41,723
I mean, this is home.

189
00:15:50,123 --> 00:15:52,429
[ Car door closes ]

190
00:15:52,473 --> 00:15:54,692
[ Car approaches ]

191
00:15:54,736 --> 00:15:57,217
-See, I've always dabbled
in native American arts.

192
00:15:57,260 --> 00:16:00,133
You know, nothing big, you know,
just little things that ...

193
00:16:00,176 --> 00:16:02,396
see, I'm a half-breed.

194
00:16:02,439 --> 00:16:05,094
Well, actually,
I'm 1/8th cherokee.

195
00:16:05,138 --> 00:16:06,704
-Ohh.

196
00:16:06,748 --> 00:16:08,576
-But it's the best thing
I've ever done.

197
00:16:08,619 --> 00:16:10,882
I mean, you know, I find
art comes natural to our people,

198
00:16:10,926 --> 00:16:12,014
don't you?

199
00:16:12,058 --> 00:16:13,015
-Yeah.

200
00:16:13,059 --> 00:16:14,582
-You guys tried the corn dogs?

201
00:16:14,625 --> 00:16:16,192
-[ Chuckles ]

202
00:16:16,236 --> 00:16:18,151
-Could never get your daddy
to wear it ...

203
00:16:18,194 --> 00:16:20,196
too little for him.

204
00:16:22,894 --> 00:16:24,984
-Hey, you seen miri?

205
00:16:25,027 --> 00:16:26,768
-Not yet.

206
00:16:26,811 --> 00:16:30,032
She called earlier,
said she'd be here soon.

207
00:16:30,076 --> 00:16:33,427
Can't count on her for anything.

208
00:16:33,470 --> 00:16:34,863
There.

209
00:16:34,906 --> 00:16:37,170
You look real nice.

210
00:16:37,213 --> 00:16:38,301
-[ Clears throat ]

211
00:16:38,345 --> 00:16:39,911
[ Keys jingle ]

212
00:16:39,955 --> 00:16:42,088
[ Engine sputtering ]

213
00:16:42,131 --> 00:16:44,829
[ Musical alarm sounds ]

214
00:16:44,873 --> 00:16:45,830
[ Keys jingle ]

215
00:16:45,874 --> 00:16:48,224
-Oh, fuck you.

216
00:16:48,268 --> 00:16:50,052
[ Keys jingle ]

217
00:16:50,096 --> 00:16:51,706
[ Musical alarm sounds ]

218
00:16:51,749 --> 00:16:54,361
[ Singing in native language
in distance ]

219
00:16:58,495 --> 00:17:01,194
-Thanks for everything, Jim.

220
00:17:01,237 --> 00:17:04,806
-Don't worry about it.

221
00:17:04,849 --> 00:17:08,549
You go get your seat.

222
00:17:08,592 --> 00:17:10,159
-[ Exhales loudly ]

223
00:17:10,203 --> 00:17:11,465
Coming?

224
00:17:11,508 --> 00:17:14,816
-Nah. I'm gonna stay here.

225
00:17:20,865 --> 00:17:23,781
[ Singing in native language
continues ]

226
00:17:57,163 --> 00:18:02,429
[ Singing in native language
continues ]

227
00:18:30,935 --> 00:18:32,937
[ Singing fades ]

228
00:18:35,244 --> 00:18:37,246
-[ Exhales loudly ]

229
00:18:45,254 --> 00:18:48,518
-Does cufe plan to stay here
forever?

230
00:18:48,562 --> 00:18:52,348
-I don't know.
Did you ask him?

231
00:18:52,392 --> 00:18:55,308
-No.

232
00:18:55,351 --> 00:18:57,266
Don't you think he needs
to get out of here?

233
00:18:57,310 --> 00:18:58,659
-[ Scoffs ]

234
00:18:58,702 --> 00:19:01,531
Probably would be
the best thing for him.

235
00:19:04,230 --> 00:19:06,971
-He could stay with me
for a while.

236
00:19:09,235 --> 00:19:11,715
-Tell him that.

237
00:19:13,326 --> 00:19:16,590
-[ Slurps ]

238
00:19:16,633 --> 00:19:18,635
Good coffee.

239
00:19:20,550 --> 00:19:22,030
-You know your daddy.

240
00:19:22,073 --> 00:19:24,075
He could always make the best.

241
00:19:24,119 --> 00:19:27,383
-Why are you acting weird?

242
00:19:27,427 --> 00:19:29,429
-I don't know what you mean.
I'm not acting weird.

243
00:19:29,472 --> 00:19:31,213
-You haven't looked me
in the eye all day.

244
00:19:31,257 --> 00:19:33,302
-My husband just died.
How do you expect me to act?

245
00:19:33,346 --> 00:19:35,086
-No, no, it's not that

246
00:19:35,130 --> 00:19:37,915
